Classification.Comment: The 1p36.32p36.12 deletion (Chr1:4481271_20530242del) identified here is an interstitial deletion on the short arm of chromosome 1. This 16Mb deletion contains 348 genes, 116 of which are OMIM associated including KCNAB2, RERE, UBE4B, CASZI, PDPN, and SPEN, which are thought to be contributory to the 1p36 deletion syndrome phenotype. Interstitial deletions such as the one identified in this individual are present in approximately 29% of affected individuals with 1p36 deletion syndrome [https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK1191/]].
